    #plaintext
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-8
            :markdown

              `peptagram` converts protoemics data into an HTML5 visualization, which is instantly:

              - executable: *runs on any modern webbrowser*
              - cross-platform: *everyone has a webbrowser*
              - self-contained: *just zip directory and send by email*
              - publishable: *installable on any server, even on Dropbox*

              `peptagram` is not meant to replace heavy-duty tools such as [peptide-shaker](https://code.google.com/p/peptide-shaker/) or the [TPP PepXMLViewer](http://tools.proteomecenter.org/wiki/index.php?title=TPP_Tutorial). Instead, it provides a useful overview of proteomics experiments in a convenient format for end-users.

    #tintedtext
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-8
            :markdown
              ## Installation

              To install, you need to have installed Python and the preferably, pip - the Python installer. Then, on the command-line:

                  pip install peptagram

              This should install `peptagram` and its dependencies: `pymzml` and `uniprot`.

